For example: - Row1,1-2: includes (1,1) - Row1,2-3: includes (1,3) - Row3,1-2: includes (3,1) - Row3,2-3: includes (3,3) - Column1, rows1-2: includes (1,1) - Column1, rows2-3: includes (3,1) - Column3, rows1-2: includes (1,3) - Column3, rows2-3: includes (3,3) So, all vertical rectangles are covered by the corners as well. Therefore, the four corner squares form a hitting set of size 4. Therefore, 4 guesses are sufficient. But is it necessary? Could we do it in 3?
